WHERE: Used to filter records based on a condition.

SELECT * FROM Employees WHERE Salary > 50000;
ORDER BY: Used to sort the result set.


SELECT * FROM Employees ORDER BY HireDate DESC;
GROUP BY: Used to group rows sharing a property so that aggregate functions can be applied to each group.


SELECT COUNT(*), Department FROM Employees GROUP BY Department;
HAVING: Used to filter records that work on summarized group data.


SELECT Department, AVG(Salary) FROM Employees GROUP BY Department HAVING AVG(Salary) > 60